      • getDefaults

        public Properties getDefaults()
        Gets the bundled default properties. The default properties are included in the jar file at /psl.properties. It refers to the bundled Public Suffix List file and uses a TreeIndexFactory.
        Returns:
        the default properties

      • build

        public PublicSuffixList build(Properties properties)
                       throws IOException,
                              ClassNotFoundException
        Builds a PublicSuffixList with custom properties. It is a good idea to load the default properties and overwrite keys as required.
        Parameters:
        properties - the properties for building the PublicSuffixList.
        Returns:
        a public suffix list build with the properties
        Throws:
        ClassNotFoundException - If the property PROPERTY_INDEX_FACTORY is not a IndexFactory implementation
        IOException - If the property PROPERTY_LIST_FILE can't be read as a file
        See Also:
        getDefaults()
